From: Wanpeng Li <liwanp@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Dec 2013 15:23:25 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] sched/numa: Use wrapper function task_faults_idx to calculate index in group_faults
Git-commit: 82897b4fd3920ffd2456731d4f2ae1406558ef4c
References: Automatic NUMA Balancing (fate#315482)
Patch-mainline: v3.14-rc1

Use wrapper function task_faults_idx to calculate index in group_faults.

Signed-off-by: Wanpeng Li <liwanp@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Reviewed-by: Naoya Horiguchi <n-horiguchi@ah.jp.nec.com>
Acked-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
Acked-by: David Rientjes <rientjes@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra <peterz@infradead.org>
Cc: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Cc: Rik van Riel <riel@redhat.com>
Link: http://lkml.kernel.org/r/1386833006-6600-3-git-send-email-liwanp@linux.vnet.ibm.com
Signed-off-by: Ingo Molnar <mingo@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Mike Galbraith <mgalbraith@suse.de>

---
 kernel/sched/fair.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -946,7 +946,8 @@ static inline unsigned long group_faults
 	if (!p->numa_group)
 		return 0;
 
-	return p->numa_group->faults[2*nid] + p->numa_group->faults[2*nid+1];
+	return p->numa_group->faults[task_faults_idx(nid, 0)] +
+		p->numa_group->faults[task_faults_idx(nid, 1)];
 }
 
 static inline unsigned long group_faults_cpu(struct numa_group *group, int nid)
